d Dirk spend an evening hitting on women, and Dirk finds success when he meets Jill. Tensions between Robert and Dirk escalate when Dirk is continuously late to work. <br> ''Guest stars'': Toni Trucks, [[James R. Black]]\n| LineColor = E17B3F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 84\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 18\n| Title = The Boy Is Mine\n| DirectedBy = Alfonso Ribeiro\n| WrittenBy = Jewel Wormley\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2007|3|26}}\n| ShortSummary = Robert and Dirk aren't on speaking terms so Robert becomes friendly with Neesee's new partner which definitely doesn't like. <br> ''Guest star'': James R. Black\n| LineColor = E17B3F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 85\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 19\n| Title = Everything Happens for a Reason\n| DirectedBy = Alfonso Ribeiro\n| WrittenBy = Asoniti Foster\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2007|4|23}}\n| ShortSummary = After Robert lets Dirk go, he feels it was the wrong decision and so he sues him. Neesee comes clean that she hadn't met Ben by chance and that she wanted to meet her sperm donor. <br> ''Guest stars'': Toni Trucks, James R. Black, [[Anna Maria Horsford]]\n| LineColor = E17B3F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 86\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 20\n| Title = Sins of the Father\n| DirectedBy = Debbie Allen\n| WrittenBy = Chad Drew\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2007|4|30}}\n| ShortSummary = Robert begins to become attached to a single parent and her child which makes Bobby feel left out. Neesee is called upon for advice after Dirk can't look after Courtney. <br> ''Guest star'': [[Meagan Good]]\n| LineColor = E17B3F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 87\n| EpisodeNumber2 = 21\n| Title = She Blinded Me with Science\n| DirectedBy = Debbie Allen\n| WrittenBy = Stacy A. Littlejohn\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2007|5|7}}\n| ShortSummary = Robert learns of Neesee's plan to visit a sperm bank to have a baby. His relationship becomes strained after his former partner comes to stay. <br> ''Guest star'': Toni Truc