{"title_page": "Athletics at the 1956 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's shot put", "text_new": "{{AthleticsAt1956SummerOlympics}}\n[[Image:TV-icon-2.svg|thumb|110px|'''{{youtube|ZluvLLmZR7k}} Official Video''']]\n\nThese are the official results of the '''[[Athletics at the 1956 Summer Olympics|men's shot put]]''' event at the '''[[1956 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Melbourne, Australia]]. The qualifying round and the final both were held on Wednesday November 28, 1956. Fourteen shot putters from ten nations competed.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1956/ATH/mens-shot-put.html |title=Athletics at the 1956 Melbourne Summer Games: Men's Shot Put |accessdate=6 January 2018 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\n[[Parry O'Brien]] had held the [[Men's shot put world record progression|world record]] for three years.  In that time he had added a meter and a quarter to the previous record, including the current world record he had set just two months earlier.  He was also the defending champion.  On his first throw of the competition, he improved upon his own Olympic record with a 17.92m.  [[Ji\u0159\u00ed Skobla]] moved into second place with 17.39m.  In the second round, O'Brien threw a second Olympic record 18.47m, which would prove to be enough to win the competition.  [[Bill Nieder]] moved into second place with a 17.61\tm, improving to a 17.81m in the third round which proved to be enough to take silver.  While he didn't improve, O'Brien threw consistently just behind his second round mark.  His best throw was in the fifth round, his third Olympic record of the day {{T&Fcalc|18.57}}.  Any of O'Brien's last five throws would have won the competition.  Just before the 18.57, Nieder threw his best of 18.18m.  During that fifth round, [[Ken Bantum]] briefly moved into bronze medal position with a 17.48m putting the American team in a position to sweep the event, before Skobla threw three additional cm past him. On his final throw Skobla threw his best of 17.65m.<ref>https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1956/ATH/mens-shot-put-final-round.html</ref>\n\n==Medallists==\n{| {{Medallists}}\n|-\n|style=\"width:12em\"| {{flagIOCmedalist|[[Parry O'Brien]]|USA|1956 Summer}}\n|style=\"width:12em\"| {{flagIOCmedalist|[[Bill Nieder]]|USA|1956 Summer}}\n|style=\"width:12em\"| {{flagIOCmedalist|[[Ji\u0159\u00ed Skobla]]|TCH|1956 Summer}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Records==\nThese were the standing world and Olympic records (in metres) prior to the 1956 Summer Olympics.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|- \n! World Record\n| 19.25\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Parry O'Brien]]\n| [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]] ([[United States|USA]])\n| November 1, 1956\n|-\n! Olympic Record\n| 17.41\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Parry O'Brien]]\n| [[Helsinki]] ([[Finland|FIN]])\n| July 21, 1952\n|}\n\n==Final classification==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n!RANK !!align=\"left\" style=\"width: 20em\"|NAME ATHLETE!!DISTANCE\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 1.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Parry O'Brien]]|USA|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|'''18.57 m'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 2.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Bill Nieder]]|USA|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|18.18 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 3.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Ji\u0159\u00ed Skobla]]|TCH|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|17.65 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|4.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Ken Bantum]]|USA|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|17.48 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|5.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Boris Belyayev]]|URS|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|16.96 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|6.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Erik Uddebom]]|SWE|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|16.65 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|7.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Karl-Heinz Wegmann]]|EUA|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|16.63 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|8.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Georgios Tsakanikas]]|GRE|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|16.56 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|9.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Barry Donath]]|AUS|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|16.52 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|10.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Silvano Meconi]]|ITA|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|16.28 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|11.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Robert Hanlin]]|AUS|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|16.08 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|12.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Barclay Palmer]]|GBR|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|15.81 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|13.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Vladimir Loshchilov]]|URS|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|15.62 m\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|14.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Raymond Thomas (athlete)|Raymond Thomas]]|FRA|1956 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|15.31 m\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140413130544/http://www.olympic-museum.de/o-reports/report1956.htm Official Report]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070930220313/http://todor66.com/olim/1956/Athletics/Men_Shot_Put.html Results]\n\n{{OlympicsShotPut}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Athletics At The 1956 Summer Olympics - Men's Shot Put}}\n[[Category:Athletics at the 1956 Summer Olympics|M]]\n[[Category:Shot put at the Olympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{AthleticsAt1956SummerOlympics}}\n[[Image:TV-icon-2.svg|thumb|110px|'''{{youtube|ZluvLLmZR7k}} Official Video''']]\n\nThese are the official results of the '''[[Athletics at the 1956 Summer Olympics|men's shot put]]''' event at the '''[[1956 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Melbourne, Australia]]. The qualifying round and the final both were held on Wednesday November 28, 1956. Fourteen shot putters from ten nations competed.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1956/ATH/mens-shot-put.html |title=Athletics at the 1956 Melbourne Summer Games: Men's Shot Put |accessdate=6 January 2018 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\n[[Parry O'Brien]] had held the [[Men's shot put world record progression|world record]] for three years.  In that time he had added a meter and a quarter to the previous record, including the current world record he had set just two months earlier.  He was also the defending champion.  On his first throw of the competition, he improved upon his own Olympic record with a 17.92m.  [[Ji\u0159\u00ed Skobla]] moved into second place with 17.39m.  In the second round, O'Brien threw a second Olympic record 18.47m, which would prove to be enough to win the competition.  [[Bill Nieder]] moved into second place with a 17.61\tm, improving to a 17.81m in the third round which proved to be enough to take silver.  While he didn't improve, O'Brien threw consistently just behind his second round mark.  His best throw was in the fifth round, his third Olympic record of the day {{T&Fcalc|18.57}}.  Any of O'Brien's last five throws would have won the competition.  Just before the 18.57, Nieder threw his best of 18.18m.  During that fifth round, [[Ken Bantum]] briefly moved into bronze medal position with a 17.48m putting the American team in a position to sweep the event for the second time in a row, before Skobla threw three additional cm past him.  On his final throw Skobla threw his best of 17.65m.<ref>https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1956/ATH/mens-shot-put-final-round.html</ref>\n\n==Medallists==\n{| {{Medallists}}\n|-\n|style=\"width:12em\"| {{flagIOCmedalist|[[Parry O'Brien]]|USA|1956 Summer}}\n|style=\"width:12em\"| {{flagIOCmedalist|[[Bill Nieder]]|USA|1956 Summer}}\n|style=\"width:12em\"| {{flagIOCmedalist|[[Ji\u0159\u00ed Skobla]]|TCH|1956 Summer}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Records==\nThese were the standing world and Olympic records (in metres) prior to the 1956 Summer Olympics.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|- \n! World Record\n| 19.25\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Parry O'Brien]]\n| [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]] ([[United States|USA]])\n| November 1, 1956\n|-\n! Olympic Record\n| 17.41\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Parry O'Brien]]\n| [[Helsinki]] ([[Finland|FIN]])\n| July 21, 1952\n|}\n\n==Final classification==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n!RANK !!align=\"left\" style=\"width: